    feat(mdm): complete Phase 6 — wire real dedup/quality engine into war room, add merge approvals + version history + AI anomaly detection
    
    Was broken/disconnected before this:
    - War room UI rendered static fake sample data (mdm-model.json), never touched
      the real Levenshtein dedup + quality-scoring engine (mdm-core.js) that
      /api/mdm/analysis and /api/mdm/summary already used.
    - 'RUN AI ANALYSIS' button called /api/mdm/query, which didn't exist -> 404.
    - No merge suggestions, change approvals, or version history existed anywhere.
    
    Added:
    - GET /api/mdm/detail: real records+duplicate clusters+merge log from the
      actual engine, replacing the disconnected static sample file.
    - POST /api/mdm/merge: approve/reject a duplicate cluster. Approved merges
      retire the losing record from the in-memory dataset (real golden-record
      operation). Every decision (approved or rejected) is appended to
      MDM_MERGE_LOG -> this is the version history / change-approval audit trail.
    - GET /api/mdm/merge-history: read the log.
    - POST /api/mdm/query: AI anomaly detection + merge-survivor recommendations
      via Groq (SP.mdm system prompt added).
    - War room UI: Merge Suggestions section (approve/reject buttons per cluster),
      Change History section (rendered from the log), record-level validation
      issues surfaced inline, KPIs/domains/records all now driven by /api/mdm/detail.
    
    Verified locally: approve retires the record and drops the duplicate count,
    reject logs the decision without retiring, bad requests 400 cleanly, missing
    Groq key fails gracefully (500 w/ message) instead of crashing.
    
    Domains covered: customer, vendor, gl (seed data only has these 3 of the 10
    listed in the Phase 6 doc — product/employee/asset/location/etc. need seed
    data added to mdm-seed-data.json + FIELD_WEIGHTS/REQUIRED_FIELDS in mdm-core.js
    before they'll show up; the engine itself is domain-agnostic and will pick
    them up automatically once seeded).

